Constable Tshepo Tladi died on Thursday night after he was shot in the head with an R5 rifle. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police commissioner Lieutenant General Deliwe de Lange has expressed her sadness at the death of an on-duty officer.Constable Tshepo Tladi died on Thursday night after he was shot in the head with an R5 rifle at a filling station in Katlehong.The constable was part of a group of policemen who were responding to an alleged robbery at the garage He was shot by one of the suspects upon arrival.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)